text: Okeelala Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Okeelala is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "splashing water". A variant transliteration is "Okolalah Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Lee County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Prentiss County, Mississippi
title: Okeelala Creek
